====Noun====
'''till'''

# [[glacial|Glacial]] drift consisting of a mixture of clay, sand, pebbles and boulders.

===Etymology 4===
Old English ''[[tilian]]''

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To [[develop]] so as to improve or prepare for usage; to [[cultivate]] (said of knowledge, virtue, mind etc).
# {{transitive}} To [[work]] or cultivate ([[soil]]); to prepare for growing vegatation and crops.
# {{intransitive}} To cultivate soil.

====Quotations====
*{{RQ:Authorized Version}} Genesis, II, 5
*: And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the LORD God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to '''till''' the ground. 

